trans-unit.source: Represents a cached LINQ to Entities query.
Provides for compilation and caching of queries for reuse.
Conceptually this class contains a single `Compile` method with several overloads.
You call the `Compile` method to create a new delegate to represent the compiled query.
The delegate, when invoked with the <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> input parameter and other parameter values, produces some result (such as an <xref:System.Linq.IQueryable%601> instance).
The query is translated and cached when the delegate is invoked for the first time.
Creates a new delegate that represents the compiled LINQ to Entities query.
For more information and examples, see [Compiled Queries (LINQ to Entities)](~/docs/framework/data/adonet/ef/language-reference/compiled-queries-linq-to-entities.md).
